<br>
A young man stumbles through the sand-blasted waste of a desert. He goes on without knowing why, and with nothing to look forward to in the distance. He has no provisions, and he is as alone as one would ever imagine. His skin is baked by the ever-burning sun, always overhead. He sees mirage after mirage, but he has the strength of mind still to disregard them. One, of a beautiful woman beckoning to him to come to her side, another, of a crystalline lake, with a trout jumping in the light breeze. <br>
<br>
He shakes his head, and trudges on. He knows that these seemingly wondrous things are not truly there. It takes all his will every moment to take the next step, and the step after. He wears rags, that barely cover him, and certainty do not help hide his battered body from the desert sun. <br>
<br>
Finally, he can take it no more. He sinks down to his knees. He, being a pious man, prays to God. “Lord God my savior! What have I done to warrant such punishment as what you have given me? I, a son of yours, am lost. I have lost my way, in this desert, this thrice-damned desert! I see no one and nothing with which to quench my thirst, or to hide me from the heat! Please O God in heaven....please help your supplicant!” <br>
<br>
With this, he falls face down onto the sand. He is totally spent. He could not move another muscle in his body if there was pure water an inch away. He hears a voice. “You who would have requested aid from the Almighty, he has granted your wish. You will be given the strength to carry on. But in this condition, you must carry on unto the end of this bright desert. No matter how much you must suffer for His cause, you must continue on. If you do not meet this request, you will surely perish.” <br>
<br>
The man feels holy light flow into his battered body. He feels his muscles rejuvenated, and his thirst and hunger relinquish their hold on him. He rises to his feet, but the Holy Angel of Mercy has vanished. “Thank you, O God! I will not let you down! I will go unto the end of this desert! I will make you proud you helped me! There is nothing in this world which could prevent me from keeping my promise to you! <br>
<br>
And so, he wanders now through the bright desert, still barely hanging on to life, but never, ever letting go, because he made a promise to God, and he intends to keep it, no matter how much he will suffer.<br>
